This file contains CISCO packet tracer practical.
I. Connecting two pc using Cross-over cable
- The pc are given static ip address 10.10.10.1 & 10.10.10.2 with subnetmask of 255.255.255.0 
- To check the connection between the pc use commannd -" ping 10.10.10.2"

II. Connecting PCs with switch
- 2960 Switch is connected with 4PC devices using Cross-over cable
- The pc are given static ip address 10.1.1.1,  10.1.1.2, 10.1.1.3, 10.1.1.5 with subnetmask of 255.255.255.0 
- To check the connection between the pc use commannd -" ping 10.10.10.2"

III. Connecting with Router
- 2911 router is connected with two 2960 switches along with PC devices using Cross-over cable
- Switch 1 is connected to router gigabitEthernet 0/1 and Switch 2 as gigabitEthernet 0/2
- The Static ip address given to pcs connected with switch 1 are 192.168.0.2 and 192.168.0.3 and Switch 2 are 192.168.10.2 and 192.168.10.3 with subnet mask of 255.255.255.0
- Default gateway for Switch 1 pc devices is 192.168.0.1 and Switch 2 is 192.168.10.1
- The router is configures as  
(#exit
#enter
#en
#config t
#int g 0/1
#ip address 192.168.0.1 255.255.255.0
#no shut
#exit
#exit
#write memory

#en
#config t
#int g 0/2
#ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0
#no shut
#exit
#exit
#write memory
- To check the connection between the pc use commannd -" ping 192.168.10.2"
